Module mesakit.map.geography
Package com.telenav.mesakit.map.geography

Enum Precision

java.lang.Object
java.lang.Enum<Precision>
com.telenav.mesakit.map.geography.Precision
All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable, Comparable<Precision>, java.lang.constant.Constable
public enum Precision extends Enum<Precision>
Decimal precision for Angle, Latitude, Longitude, Width, Height and Heading values when they are stored as integral primitives.

DM{N} is a value that has N digits after the decimal.

For example, 85 degrees in DM6 is 85.000000 which is 85,000,000 as an integer.

In DM7, 85 degrees is 850,000,000.

Author:
jonathanl (shibo)

      public int toDecimal​(double degrees)
      Convert degrees to decimal in this precision. Note that this method is here to avoid allocation for efficiency purposes only and should ONLY be used when a hot spot is noticed in a profiler.
